project_descr: Sierra Leone realizing the potential of a rapid spread of HIV in a post conflict setting has made significant gains to address HIV and AIDS epidemic within its context.

outputs.output_descr: Promoting Gender Equality and Women's Rights. Parliament and other national institutions assisted to implement its individual mandate in a participatory, transparent and accountable manner.

The 2012 HIV & AIDS annual work plan is a continuum of UNDP’s interventions in complementing the efforts of the government and other development partners for a sustained national response to HIV and AIDS in Sierra Leone as per UN division of labour and UNDP’s area of comparative advantage. In the past year decentralizing the response to HIV and AIDS by introducing the Community Capacity Enhancement through community conversations (CCE-CC) was prioritized.
